Nintendo has unveiled a new low cost handheld games console aimed at taking on the threat from mobile phone games.

The 2DS, which has a shallow wedge-like design and two screens, will cost £109 ($129) when it goes on sale on October 12th.

It is aimed at children and Nintendo hopes the low cost will persuade parents to buy it instead of a smartphone or tablet.

