The firm is going after ‘not just consumers who have necessarily a phone or tablet,’ and want a taste of Nintendo's game fare, ‘but all consumers, especially younger consumers,’ Reggie Fils-Aime, president of Nintendo of America, said.

‘Nintendo has one of the strongest and most diverse video game lineups in our history,’ he claimed.

‘Today we’re making those unique Nintendo experiences more accessible and affordable.’

Experts say the surprise launch could pay off.

